“Stop him,” I shouted. “Where is he? Stop him.”

“He’s gone,” she said, politely disengaging herself from my unintentional embrace.

“Why the deuce did you—” I began, but did not finish my sentence, rushed away, put on shoes, trousers and overcoat, ran downstairs and out into the street. Nobody. I went on to the corner, stood there for a while looking about me and finally went back indoors. I was alone, as Lydia had gone out very early to see some female acqua